00:15:59.912 --> 00:16:01.370 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE:
Completely ungrounded.

00:16:01.370 --> 00:16:05.860 align:middle line:84%
They are lost in space when it
comes to managing their money

00:16:05.860 --> 00:16:06.710 align:middle line:90%
and stuff like that.

00:16:06.710 --> 00:16:10.270 align:middle line:84%
And so, I consider
it a blessing that I

00:16:10.270 --> 00:16:12.110 align:middle line:90%
have both of these things.

00:16:12.110 --> 00:16:12.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:16:12.910 --> 00:16:15.550 align:middle line:84%
Well, what about because,
as you say, turns out

00:16:15.550 --> 00:16:16.460 align:middle line:90%
you were good at it.

00:16:16.460 --> 00:16:17.260 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Yeah.

00:16:17.260 --> 00:16:19.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So what about
numbers themselves,

00:16:19.570 --> 00:16:22.150 align:middle line:84%
the kind of truthfulness
behind numbers?

00:16:22.150 --> 00:16:26.380 align:middle line:84%
Did you find that there was
a kind of beauty in numbers?

00:16:26.380 --> 00:16:28.210 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: I
liked the puzzles.

00:16:28.210 --> 00:16:33.660 align:middle line:84%
To me, it was a puzzle, because
it all has to balance in this,

00:16:33.660 --> 00:16:35.372 align:middle line:90%
I'm not this much of a nerd, OK?

00:16:35.372 --> 00:16:36.580 align:middle line:90%
Well, actually, I kind of am.

00:16:36.580 --> 00:16:41.440 align:middle line:84%
But it's like there
is a magic to the fact

00:16:41.440 --> 00:16:43.150 align:middle line:90%
that it all has to balance.

00:16:43.150 --> 00:16:45.980 align:middle line:84%
It all has to come together
or you did it wrong.

00:16:45.980 --> 00:16:46.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:16:46.780 --> 00:16:48.242 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: And I liked that.

00:16:48.242 --> 00:16:49.200 align:middle line:90%
I really did like that.

00:16:49.200 --> 00:16:55.300 align:middle line:84%
But where I excelled, to be
honest, was in managing people.

00:16:55.300 --> 00:16:57.520 align:middle line:84%
I was an amazing
manager of people.

00:16:57.520 --> 00:17:00.310 align:middle line:84%
And so, as I went
through my career,

00:17:00.310 --> 00:17:04.060 align:middle line:84%
it became less debits and
credits and less putting teams

00:17:04.060 --> 00:17:04.930 align:middle line:90%
together.

00:17:04.930 --> 00:17:08.589 align:middle line:84%
And I was using Radleigh's
little special gift

00:17:08.589 --> 00:17:09.470 align:middle line:90%
to hire people.

00:17:09.470 --> 00:17:10.270 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:17:10.270 --> 00:17:12.130 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: Because I
would know it's like,

00:17:12.130 --> 00:17:13.279 align:middle line:90%
you're a good one.

00:17:13.279 --> 00:17:14.079 align:middle line:90%
I'll take you.

00:17:14.079 --> 00:17:14.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:17:14.890 --> 00:17:17.560 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: And plus, I
had the whole understanding

00:17:17.560 --> 00:17:19.130 align:middle line:90%
of diversity.

00:17:19.130 --> 00:17:23.920 align:middle line:84%
And so, I would hire like a
series of accounting managers

00:17:23.920 --> 00:17:26.200 align:middle line:90%
that needed each other.

00:17:26.200 --> 00:17:28.150 align:middle line:90%
This dude was the SEC dude.

00:17:28.150 --> 00:17:30.370 align:middle line:84%
But this girl knows
nothing about SEC.

00:17:30.370 --> 00:17:34.570 align:middle line:84%
But she can wrap you around
her finger like that.

00:17:34.570 --> 00:17:35.990 align:middle line:90%
And he can't.

00:17:35.990 --> 00:17:38.860 align:middle line:84%
And I literally had people from
the marketing department come

00:17:38.860 --> 00:17:41.110 align:middle line:84%
to me and say, will
you hire my staff?

00:17:41.110 --> 00:17:43.660 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, I don't know
anything about marketing.

00:17:43.660 --> 00:17:45.250 align:middle line:90%
And they're like, we don't care.

00:17:45.250 --> 00:17:48.520 align:middle line:84%
When I left accounting, I had
150 people working for me.

00:17:48.520 --> 00:17:49.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Wow.

00:17:49.630 --> 00:17:50.500 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Yeah.

00:17:50.500 --> 00:17:55.300 align:middle line:84%
And I had the happiest
team of any department.

00:17:55.300 --> 00:17:57.100 align:middle line:90%
And they were productive.

00:17:57.100 --> 00:17:58.600 align:middle line:90%
And they loved each other.

00:17:58.600 --> 00:18:02.630 align:middle line:84%
But I was using that sixth sense
to put these teams together.

00:18:02.630 --> 00:18:03.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:18:03.430 --> 00:18:03.640 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:18:03.640 --> 00:18:04.440 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:18:04.440 --> 00:18:05.370 align:middle line:90%
I can see that.

00:18:05.370 --> 00:18:07.870 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's what
every corporation needs

00:18:07.870 --> 00:18:09.060 align:middle line:90%
is someone who can do that.

00:18:09.060 --> 00:18:10.480 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: Well, and
that's why I was popular.

00:18:10.480 --> 00:18:11.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:18:11.320 --> 00:18:14.860 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: Suddenly, I went
from my childhood being the way

00:18:14.860 --> 00:18:18.070 align:middle line:90%
it was to being here I am.

00:18:18.070 --> 00:18:20.020 align:middle line:90%
Like everybody wants to hire me.

00:18:20.020 --> 00:18:20.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:18:20.890 --> 00:18:22.510 align:middle line:84%
You know, this whole
thing about how

00:18:22.510 --> 00:18:24.220 align:middle line:84%
to order a corporation
in the right way,

00:18:24.220 --> 00:18:26.590 align:middle line:84%
because so many of
them are done poorly.

00:18:26.590 --> 00:18:29.500 align:middle line:84%
There was a man I interviewed
years ago named Rob Williams,

00:18:29.500 --> 00:18:31.960 align:middle line:84%
and he served as,
what he called,

00:18:31.960 --> 00:18:34.330 align:middle line:84%
the CSO or chief
shamanic officer.

00:18:34.330 --> 00:18:35.350 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Oh, yay.

00:18:35.350 --> 00:18:36.150 align:middle line:90%
Good title.

00:18:36.150 --> 00:18:37.750 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And was
talking about how

00:18:37.750 --> 00:18:40.582 align:middle line:84%
this was so necessary
in the world of business

00:18:40.582 --> 00:18:42.040 align:middle line:84%
to have people like
you, people who

00:18:42.040 --> 00:18:44.470 align:middle line:84%
can see underneath
things, behind things,

00:18:44.470 --> 00:18:48.370 align:middle line:84%
and see the deeper truth, and
have a position for someone who

00:18:48.370 --> 00:18:50.170 align:middle line:90%
can do that on staff.

00:18:50.170 --> 00:18:52.720 align:middle line:84%
So I can see why you
were just pure gold.

00:18:52.720 --> 00:18:54.270 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: Well,
and I was fun.

00:18:54.270 --> 00:18:54.530 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:18:54.530 --> 00:18:55.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:18:55.330 --> 00:19:00.062 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: It's like
accountants can be dry or fun.

00:19:00.062 --> 00:19:01.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: They can be fun.

00:19:01.830 --> 00:19:04.170 align:middle line:84%
OK, well, let's talk about
numerology, numbers, numbers,

00:19:04.170 --> 00:19:04.970 align:middle line:90%
numbers.

00:19:04.970 --> 00:19:07.900 align:middle line:84%
I thought might you have
had a unique relationship

00:19:07.900 --> 00:19:11.740 align:middle line:84%
to numerology because
of your life in numbers.

00:19:11.740 --> 00:19:13.720 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Not necessarily.

00:19:13.720 --> 00:19:17.710 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of like even
though I was an accountant,

00:19:17.710 --> 00:19:19.270 align:middle line:90%
I didn't do my own taxes.

00:19:19.270 --> 00:19:20.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, OK, gotcha.

00:19:20.570 --> 00:19:23.560 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: And so, if I was
going to go after spirituality,

00:19:23.560 --> 00:19:27.160 align:middle line:84%
if I was going to go after
the right side of my brain,

00:19:27.160 --> 00:19:28.550 align:middle line:90%
I didn't want to like--

00:19:28.550 --> 00:19:29.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:19:29.350 --> 00:19:31.390 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: So I
studied numerology.

00:19:31.390 --> 00:19:32.687 align:middle line:90%
I learned about it.

00:19:32.687 --> 00:19:35.270 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But there was no kind
of natural crossover affinity.

00:19:35.270 --> 00:19:35.755 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: It wasn't.

00:19:35.755 --> 00:19:36.100 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:19:36.100 --> 00:19:38.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, OK, so let's
go back to tarot for a minute.

00:19:38.170 --> 00:19:39.670 align:middle line:90%
So you're fascinated with tarot.

00:19:39.670 --> 00:19:40.030 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Yeah.

00:19:40.030 --> 00:19:41.925 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now you've
decided to perfect

00:19:41.925 --> 00:19:44.020 align:middle line:90%
or refine the scary cards.

00:19:44.020 --> 00:19:44.820 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Yeah.

00:19:44.820 --> 00:19:46.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, and let's
go further into it.

00:19:46.240 --> 00:19:48.282 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: Well, I mean,
really what it was was

00:19:48.282 --> 00:19:50.590 align:middle line:84%
I wanted the deck that
I had always wanted.

00:19:50.590 --> 00:19:53.320 align:middle line:84%
That's really what
it boiled down to.

00:19:53.320 --> 00:19:57.550 align:middle line:84%
Because it took me, I mean, I
have like 70 something decks

00:19:57.550 --> 00:20:01.060 align:middle line:84%
at home in a box, mostly
because I would buy the deck

00:20:01.060 --> 00:20:04.360 align:middle line:84%
and go, eh, and
there it would go.

00:20:04.360 --> 00:20:09.340 align:middle line:84%
And so, I really, really
wanted people not to be afraid.

00:20:09.340 --> 00:20:14.500 align:middle line:84%
I consider my twin life purposes
to be to take the fear out

00:20:14.500 --> 00:20:18.240 align:middle line:84%
of spirituality and show people
how to have a magical life.

00:20:18.240 --> 00:20:20.520 align:middle line:90%
That's what I really get off on.

00:20:20.520 --> 00:20:21.750 align:middle line:90%
I love that.

00:20:21.750 --> 00:20:23.910 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't want
to water down ,

00:20:23.910 --> 00:20:26.690 align:middle line:84%
tarot because then
it's not very useful.

00:20:26.690 --> 00:20:27.490 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:20:27.490 --> 00:20:30.510 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: Because
tarot represents life.

00:20:30.510 --> 00:20:32.430 align:middle line:90%
Sorrow happens in life.

00:20:32.430 --> 00:20:34.200 align:middle line:90%
You can't take it out.

00:20:34.200 --> 00:20:36.120 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't
have to be a heart

00:20:36.120 --> 00:20:38.339 align:middle line:84%
with three swords with blood
dripping out the bottom.

00:20:38.339 --> 00:20:39.381 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, exactly.

00:20:39.381 --> 00:20:39.840 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: You know?

00:20:39.840 --> 00:20:41.340 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't have to be that.

00:20:41.340 --> 00:20:44.460 align:middle line:84%
That's a hold back
to 600 years ago when

00:20:44.460 --> 00:20:46.290 align:middle line:90%
tarot started getting created.

00:20:46.290 --> 00:20:48.010 align:middle line:90%
And it was a tough time.

00:20:48.010 --> 00:20:51.700 align:middle line:84%
It was rough in life, and
people were illiterate.

00:20:51.700 --> 00:20:55.310 align:middle line:84%
And so, they needed something
really graphic to explain it.

00:20:55.310 --> 00:20:56.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Visceral, yeah.

00:20:56.790 --> 00:20:59.850 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: And what my
perception was that, well,

00:20:59.850 --> 00:21:02.400 align:middle line:84%
we've had 600 years
to evolve, because I

00:21:02.400 --> 00:21:04.050 align:middle line:90%
believe in reincarnation.

00:21:04.050 --> 00:21:05.580 align:middle line:84%
What I'm looking
around and seeing

00:21:05.580 --> 00:21:06.955 align:middle line:84%
is a whole bunch
of people who've

00:21:06.955 --> 00:21:10.740 align:middle line:84%
gone through enough lifetimes
to be incredibly sensitive,

00:21:10.740 --> 00:21:13.110 align:middle line:90%
incredibly sensitive.

00:21:13.110 --> 00:21:17.100 align:middle line:84%
And they may have this
sense of remembering tarot

00:21:17.100 --> 00:21:19.530 align:middle line:84%
from a past life when
they could tolerate it.

00:21:19.530 --> 00:21:23.250 align:middle line:84%
But now, they're looking at
it and going, not so much.

00:21:23.250 --> 00:21:24.960 align:middle line:90%
And we have television.

00:21:24.960 --> 00:21:27.000 align:middle line:84%
When was the last time
you saw a show or a movie

00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:29.440 align:middle line:84%
where the card that
flipped down wasn't death?

00:21:29.440 --> 00:21:32.400 align:middle line:84%
Really, it's just the only
card they have, right?

00:21:32.400 --> 00:21:34.365 align:middle line:84%
They've got it in a
stockroom somewhere.

00:21:34.365 --> 00:21:35.390 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, right.

00:21:35.390 --> 00:21:36.320 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: It's the
only one they have.

00:21:36.320 --> 00:21:37.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's the
only death card.

00:21:37.500 --> 00:21:38.650 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: That's right.

00:21:38.650 --> 00:21:42.520 align:middle line:84%
And so, I wanted to, first
of all, take the fear out.

00:21:42.520 --> 00:21:43.320 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:21:43.320 --> 00:21:45.400 align:middle line:84%
So go through, and
it's like, fine,

00:21:45.400 --> 00:21:49.840 align:middle line:84%
we don't need the heart with
the blood running through it.

00:21:49.840 --> 00:21:55.380 align:middle line:84%
What about an arc angel holding
a woman in a gentle embrace

00:21:55.380 --> 00:21:57.310 align:middle line:90%
while she cries on his shoulder?

00:21:57.310 --> 00:21:58.110 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:21:58.110 --> 00:22:01.380 align:middle line:84%
Same message, sorrow,
sadness, but also

00:22:01.380 --> 00:22:04.810 align:middle line:84%
adding the message of angels
are with you, and they love you,

00:22:04.810 --> 00:22:06.440 align:middle line:84%
and that will help
you get through it.

00:22:06.440 --> 00:22:07.410 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love it.

00:22:07.410 --> 00:22:09.720 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: When I was
learning tarot in my 20s,

00:22:09.720 --> 00:22:12.990 align:middle line:84%
I finally found a deck I could
tolerate, so I bought two.

00:22:12.990 --> 00:22:15.450 align:middle line:84%
And I took a black
Sharpie and I wrote

00:22:15.450 --> 00:22:17.910 align:middle line:84%
on every card what they
mean, because there's

00:22:17.910 --> 00:22:18.990 align:middle line:90%
no words on tarot.

00:22:18.990 --> 00:22:22.260 align:middle line:84%
It was done that way
to scare you out of it,

00:22:22.260 --> 00:22:24.580 align:middle line:84%
to make you think,
you can't do this.

00:22:24.580 --> 00:22:29.220 align:middle line:84%
It's too hard, to memorize
all these multiple meanings.

00:22:29.220 --> 00:22:31.500 align:middle line:84%
And so, when I
created my first deck,

00:22:31.500 --> 00:22:33.120 align:middle line:84%
I was like, I did
that for myself.

00:22:33.120 --> 00:22:34.530 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do it for them.

00:22:34.530 --> 00:22:37.080 align:middle line:84%
Let's put words, phrases
at the bottom of the card.

00:22:37.080 --> 00:22:40.640 align:middle line:84%
Let's let them open the
box and immediately be

00:22:40.640 --> 00:22:41.440 align:middle line:90%
able to use these.

00:22:41.440 --> 00:22:42.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, it
makes so much sense.

00:22:42.650 --> 00:22:43.170 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Right?

00:22:43.170 --> 00:22:43.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:22:43.610 --> 00:22:44.060 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Right.

00:22:44.060 --> 00:22:45.180 align:middle line:90%
Make it easy.

00:22:45.180 --> 00:22:46.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because usually,
you have a little book

00:22:46.170 --> 00:22:47.400 align:middle line:90%
that goes along with it.

00:22:47.400 --> 00:22:48.775 align:middle line:84%
Then you have to
go over, and you

00:22:48.775 --> 00:22:50.510 align:middle line:84%
have to look up the
number in the book.

00:22:50.510 --> 00:22:52.950 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, it makes logical sense
to have the information

00:22:52.950 --> 00:22:53.540 align:middle line:90%
right in front of you.

00:22:53.540 --> 00:22:54.560 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: And
there is a booklet,

00:22:54.560 --> 00:22:56.050 align:middle line:90%
and it's good to read it.

00:22:56.050 --> 00:22:59.790 align:middle line:84%
But I wanted people to be able
to pull them out, use them

00:22:59.790 --> 00:23:01.920 align:middle line:90%
right then, and not be afraid.

00:23:01.920 --> 00:23:02.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:23:02.830 --> 00:23:03.630 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:23:03.630 --> 00:23:06.780 align:middle line:84%
So we're going to get into
the notion of interpretation

00:23:06.780 --> 00:23:07.930 align:middle line:90%
when you're reading cards.

00:23:07.930 --> 00:23:09.690 align:middle line:84%
Some people have
intuitive ability.

00:23:09.690 --> 00:23:10.610 align:middle line:90%
Some don't.

00:23:10.610 --> 00:23:11.730 align:middle line:84%
And they're just
left with the words,

00:23:11.730 --> 00:23:13.220 align:middle line:90%
and they're left with the image.

00:23:13.220 --> 00:23:15.760 align:middle line:84%
Well, let's talk about
that for a moment.

00:23:15.760 --> 00:23:18.300 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: I believe that
anybody can play the piano.

00:23:18.300 --> 00:23:21.330 align:middle line:84%
Maybe not everybody
is a concert pianist.

00:23:21.330 --> 00:23:22.630 align:middle line:90%
But anybody can play the piano.

00:23:22.630 --> 00:23:23.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: True.

00:23:23.430 --> 00:23:25.170 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: I
believe that we all

00:23:25.170 --> 00:23:27.300 align:middle line:84%
have a touch of the
divine within us,

00:23:27.300 --> 00:23:28.860 align:middle line:90%
because that's who we are.

00:23:28.860 --> 00:23:32.270 align:middle line:84%
We have a bit of the magic
of the divine inside us.

00:23:32.270 --> 00:23:36.300 align:middle line:84%
So I believe that
everybody has divine gifts.

00:23:36.300 --> 00:23:39.090 align:middle line:84%
It's do you want
to use them or not?

00:23:39.090 --> 00:23:40.530 align:middle line:90%
Are you afraid of them?

00:23:40.530 --> 00:23:41.820 align:middle line:90%
Are you going to practice?

00:23:41.820 --> 00:23:44.640 align:middle line:84%
Because it is practice,
practice, practice.

00:23:44.640 --> 00:23:48.890 align:middle line:84%
So anybody can do
this if they want it.

00:23:48.890 --> 00:23:51.930 align:middle line:84%
But you were talking about the
whole intuitive part, the thing

00:23:51.930 --> 00:23:54.000 align:middle line:84%
about tarot when I
teach it to my students

00:23:54.000 --> 00:23:56.430 align:middle line:90%
is that, OK, there's a picture.

00:23:56.430 --> 00:23:58.110 align:middle line:90%
There are words.

00:23:58.110 --> 00:24:00.930 align:middle line:84%
And there are meanings
behind all of this.

00:24:00.930 --> 00:24:02.790 align:middle line:90%
There's tons of symbolism.

00:24:02.790 --> 00:24:05.610 align:middle line:84%
You can go down that rabbit
hole if you want about all

00:24:05.610 --> 00:24:06.810 align:middle line:90%
of that symbolism.

00:24:06.810 --> 00:24:08.580 align:middle line:90%
I certainly do.

00:24:08.580 --> 00:24:10.600 align:middle line:90%
Or you can not.

00:24:10.600 --> 00:24:12.720 align:middle line:90%
It's your call.

00:24:12.720 --> 00:24:14.070 align:middle line:90%
But you have to trust.

00:24:14.070 --> 00:24:15.190 align:middle line:90%
You have to have faith.

00:24:15.190 --> 00:24:17.100 align:middle line:10%
You have to look at
the cards and go,

00:24:17.100 --> 00:24:19.680 align:middle line:10%
where are my eyes drawn?

00:24:19.680 --> 00:24:21.570 align:middle line:84%
And I teach my
students, it's like,

00:24:21.570 --> 00:24:23.457 align:middle line:84%
are your eyes drawn
to a particular phrase

00:24:23.457 --> 00:24:24.540 align:middle line:90%
at the bottom of the card?

00:24:24.540 --> 00:24:26.490 align:middle line:84%
Are your eyes drawn
to the picture?

00:24:26.490 --> 00:24:29.740 align:middle line:84%
Are you thinking about
the meaning of the card?

00:24:29.740 --> 00:24:32.010 align:middle line:90%
Where intuitively are you?

00:24:32.010 --> 00:24:34.140 align:middle line:84%
I had a student
just this past week,

00:24:34.140 --> 00:24:38.490 align:middle line:84%
lovely, lovely young
woman and really gifted

00:24:38.490 --> 00:24:41.310 align:middle line:84%
but in her head a
little too much.

00:24:41.310 --> 00:24:43.950 align:middle line:90%
And she pulled the dreamer card.

00:24:43.950 --> 00:24:47.910 align:middle line:84%
And her question was, is my
cat, who just passed over,

00:24:47.910 --> 00:24:50.520 align:middle line:84%
still with me following
me as a guide?

00:24:50.520 --> 00:24:53.380 align:middle line:84%
And she looked at the card and
it says, take a leap of faith.

00:24:53.380 --> 00:24:55.830 align:middle line:84%
You know, go after what you
want, blah, blah, blah, blah.

00:24:55.830 --> 00:24:58.800 align:middle line:84%
And she raises her hand, and
I'm like, what is it dear?

00:24:58.800 --> 00:25:01.090 align:middle line:84%
And she's like, well, this
just doesn't make sense

00:25:01.090 --> 00:25:01.650 align:middle line:90%
to my question.

00:25:01.650 --> 00:25:02.983 align:middle line:90%
And I said, what's the question?

00:25:02.983 --> 00:25:04.530 align:middle line:84%
And she told me,
is my cat with me?

00:25:04.530 --> 00:25:05.460 align:middle line:90%
She just passed over.

00:25:05.460 --> 00:25:07.080 align:middle line:90%
And I said look at the picture.

00:25:07.080 --> 00:25:10.490 align:middle line:84%
And the picture was a
young man with his dog.

00:25:10.490 --> 00:25:12.030 align:middle line:90%
And she started to cry.

00:25:12.030 --> 00:25:12.973 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:25:12.973 --> 00:25:13.890 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: You know?

00:25:13.890 --> 00:25:15.480 align:middle line:84%
It's just a matter of
getting out of your head.

00:25:15.480 --> 00:25:15.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:25:15.840 --> 00:25:16.640 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:25:16.640 --> 00:25:18.930 align:middle line:90%
That's a good explanation.

00:25:18.930 --> 00:25:22.280 align:middle line:84%
OK, tarot cards, so that's why
you did what you did with it.

00:25:22.280 --> 00:25:23.800 align:middle line:90%
That was your journey with them.

00:25:23.800 --> 00:25:23.990 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Yeah.

00:25:23.990 --> 00:25:24.620 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You still do them.

00:25:24.620 --> 00:25:26.000 align:middle line:84%
Do you have new
decks coming out?

00:25:26.000 --> 00:25:26.800 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: I do.

00:25:26.800 --> 00:25:27.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You do?

00:25:27.100 --> 00:25:28.392 align:middle line:90%
When's the new deck coming out?

00:25:28.392 --> 00:25:30.170 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: Oh my
gosh, I'm so excited.

00:25:30.170 --> 00:25:31.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I want to see it.

00:25:31.640 --> 00:25:33.770 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: My newest
deck will be coming out

00:25:33.770 --> 00:25:36.560 align:middle line:90%
in October of 2020.

00:25:36.560 --> 00:25:38.947 align:middle line:84%
And it's called Angel
Guidance Tarot Cards.

00:25:38.947 --> 00:25:40.280 align:middle line:90%
And I am over the moon about it.

00:25:40.280 --> 00:25:43.620 align:middle line:84%
I have got the artist
of the century.

00:25:43.620 --> 00:25:48.650 align:middle line:84%
His name is Dan Craig,
not the 007 guy, sadly.

00:25:48.650 --> 00:25:52.250 align:middle line:84%
But I mean, this
man is so amazing.

00:25:52.250 --> 00:25:53.750 align:middle line:90%
His art is beautiful.

00:25:53.750 --> 00:25:55.800 align:middle line:90%
He's got a dry sense of humor.

00:25:55.800 --> 00:25:58.340 align:middle line:84%
He will make suggestions,
and they're always great.

00:25:58.340 --> 00:26:00.010 align:middle line:90%
But he doesn't fight me.

00:26:00.010 --> 00:26:03.480 align:middle line:84%
And he knows nothing about
tarot, which is what I go for.

00:26:03.480 --> 00:26:04.280 align:middle line:90%
I want that.

00:26:04.280 --> 00:26:05.250 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You want
interpretation.

00:26:05.250 --> 00:26:06.530 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: I don't want
people coming and going,

00:26:06.530 --> 00:26:08.025 align:middle line:90%
but where's the bloody heart?

00:26:08.025 --> 00:26:08.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:26:08.200 --> 00:26:09.325 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: It's not here.

00:26:09.325 --> 00:26:11.050 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:26:11.050 --> 00:26:14.150 align:middle line:84%
And it does some things that
I've never seen done in tarot,

00:26:14.150 --> 00:26:15.410 align:middle line:90%
so I'm excited about that.

00:26:15.410 --> 00:26:18.200 align:middle line:84%
Because after 600 years, if
you can do something new, then

00:26:18.200 --> 00:26:19.160 align:middle line:90%
good on you.

00:26:19.160 --> 00:26:19.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:26:19.960 --> 00:26:22.490 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: And i editorial
right now, which leads to art,

00:26:22.490 --> 00:26:25.560 align:middle line:84%
I am working on ascended
master tarot cards.

00:26:25.560 --> 00:26:28.920 align:middle line:84%
So that's going to come
out in October of 2021.

00:26:28.920 --> 00:26:29.720 align:middle line:90%
So I'm doing that.

00:26:29.720 --> 00:26:29.978 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Good.

00:26:29.978 --> 00:26:30.410 align:middle line:90%
Well, excellent.

00:26:30.410 --> 00:26:31.210 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Yes.

00:26:31.210 --> 00:26:33.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so do you
feel good with tarot

00:26:33.110 --> 00:26:35.490 align:middle line:84%
before we move on to runes
and some other things?

00:26:35.490 --> 00:26:35.720 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Sure.

00:26:35.720 --> 00:26:37.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because it is a
compendium of magical things.

00:26:37.850 --> 00:26:38.300 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: It is.

00:26:38.300 --> 00:26:39.675 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's
talk about runes.

00:26:39.675 --> 00:26:41.008 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Well, it's ancient.

00:26:41.008 --> 00:26:42.110 align:middle line:90%
It's way older than tarot.

00:26:42.110 --> 00:26:42.410 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:26:42.410 --> 00:26:43.827 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: I
mean, tarot is kind

00:26:43.827 --> 00:26:45.363 align:middle line:84%
of like the baby
of the compendium.

00:26:45.363 --> 00:26:46.163 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:26:46.163 --> 00:26:46.963 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:26:46.963 --> 00:26:48.360 align:middle line:90%
Runes, they feel Stone Age.

00:26:48.360 --> 00:26:50.120 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: They
do, because they are.

00:26:50.120 --> 00:26:51.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:26:51.080 --> 00:26:51.997 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: They are.

00:26:51.997 --> 00:26:54.680 align:middle line:84%
And in ancient times,
people would carve these

00:26:54.680 --> 00:26:58.730 align:middle line:84%
into their homes and
into their wagons

00:26:58.730 --> 00:27:00.935 align:middle line:84%
or sew them into
their clothes to bring

00:27:00.935 --> 00:27:03.650 align:middle line:84%
the kind of good fortune
or the kind of protection

00:27:03.650 --> 00:27:05.460 align:middle line:90%
that they were looking for.

00:27:05.460 --> 00:27:08.270 align:middle line:84%
Compendium of magical
things is really a follow

00:27:08.270 --> 00:27:09.950 align:middle line:90%
on to my work with tarot.

00:27:09.950 --> 00:27:14.510 align:middle line:84%
It's to take all these different
languages of the divine, which

00:27:14.510 --> 00:27:19.100 align:middle line:84%
is what I call them, and
in a sort of a buffet style

00:27:19.100 --> 00:27:22.130 align:middle line:84%
take the fear out of it and
make them easy to understand.

00:27:22.130 --> 00:27:24.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So now how have
you done this with runes?

00:27:24.500 --> 00:27:25.875 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: So
one of the things

00:27:25.875 --> 00:27:32.000 align:middle line:84%
that I did was I did not go
too overly deep into Odin

00:27:32.000 --> 00:27:35.710 align:middle line:84%
and his gruesome way of
having come to the runes.

00:27:35.710 --> 00:27:37.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: This was darker times.

00:27:37.060 --> 00:27:38.420 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: Darker,
times hanging upside down,

00:27:38.420 --> 00:27:39.260 align:middle line:90%
bleeding out.

00:27:39.260 --> 00:27:40.550 align:middle line:90%
Fun, yeah, no.

00:27:40.550 --> 00:27:44.000 align:middle line:84%
So kind of like, eh, let's
not bring that up too much.

00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:47.300 align:middle line:84%
OK, Odin had a lot to do with
this, as an ancient Norse god,

00:27:47.300 --> 00:27:48.320 align:middle line:90%
so cool.

00:27:48.320 --> 00:27:50.930 align:middle line:10%
Writing Compendium was an
amazing experience for me,

00:27:50.930 --> 00:27:53.210 align:middle line:10%
because I started
to research runes.

00:27:53.210 --> 00:27:54.890 align:middle line:90%
And I started to play with them.

00:27:54.890 --> 00:27:57.120 align:middle line:90%
And they were blowing me away.

00:27:57.120 --> 00:27:58.890 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's like I
would pull out a rune

00:27:58.890 --> 00:28:02.580 align:middle line:84%
and and then go read the message
for that rune and be like,

00:28:02.580 --> 00:28:04.010 align:middle line:90%
this is so spot on.

00:28:04.010 --> 00:28:05.930 align:middle line:90%
I can't believe it.

00:28:05.930 --> 00:28:07.665 align:middle line:90%
And the runes are stubborn.

00:28:07.665 --> 00:28:09.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What do
you mean by stubborn?

00:28:09.290 --> 00:28:11.910 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: Well, so like
you'd throw it back in the bag.

00:28:11.910 --> 00:28:15.850 align:middle line:84%
And the next day you come and
you pull one and it's the same.

00:28:15.850 --> 00:28:16.650 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Same one?

00:28:16.650 --> 00:28:17.750 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:28:17.750 --> 00:28:20.570 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: The runes,
they will task you.

00:28:20.570 --> 00:28:26.180 align:middle line:84%
They want you to take the
advice, do something with it.

00:28:26.180 --> 00:28:29.990 align:middle line:84%
And so, my experience with
them was either take the advice

00:28:29.990 --> 00:28:31.742 align:middle line:84%
and do something with
it, or they're just

00:28:31.742 --> 00:28:33.950 align:middle line:84%
going to hit you over and
over with the same message,

00:28:33.950 --> 00:28:35.990 align:middle line:84%
or they're going to
start goofing with you

00:28:35.990 --> 00:28:38.607 align:middle line:84%
and give you messages that
make no sense whatsoever.

00:28:38.607 --> 00:28:39.440 align:middle line:90%
It's just gibberish.

00:28:39.440 --> 00:28:41.920 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: If you ignore them,
then they'll play with you.

00:28:41.920 --> 00:28:42.370 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:28:42.370 --> 00:28:43.703 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: They'll ignore you.

00:28:43.703 --> 00:28:46.190 align:middle line:84%
It's like, you're not
taking me seriously.

00:28:46.190 --> 00:28:47.700 align:middle line:90%
But they're magical.

00:28:47.700 --> 00:28:49.310 align:middle line:90%
I love the way they feel.

00:28:49.310 --> 00:28:52.820 align:middle line:84%
In ancient times, people would
carve their own out of wood

00:28:52.820 --> 00:28:54.590 align:middle line:90%
or bone and paint their own.

00:28:54.590 --> 00:28:59.300 align:middle line:84%
But these days, they're cut into
crystals and all these kinds

00:28:59.300 --> 00:29:00.350 align:middle line:90%
of beautiful things.

00:29:00.350 --> 00:29:02.660 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they fit in
your purse, right?

00:29:02.660 --> 00:29:05.030 align:middle line:84%
You can take them
wherever you want to go.

00:29:05.030 --> 00:29:07.520 align:middle line:84%
You can very discreetly
reach into your purse

00:29:07.520 --> 00:29:08.418 align:middle line:90%
and pull a rune.

00:29:08.418 --> 00:29:10.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Pull a rune in
the middle of a business

00:29:10.460 --> 00:29:11.502 align:middle line:90%
meeting, a board meeting.

00:29:11.502 --> 00:29:13.140 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Home Depot.

00:29:13.140 --> 00:29:14.390 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:29:14.390 --> 00:29:17.510 align:middle line:90%
So they're very transportable.

00:29:17.510 --> 00:29:18.770 align:middle line:90%
And I love all that.

00:29:18.770 --> 00:29:19.910 align:middle line:90%
But they're deep.

00:29:19.910 --> 00:29:21.045 align:middle line:90%
I mean, this is not--

00:29:21.045 --> 00:29:23.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Are they I more of
a taskmaster, you're saying?

00:29:23.420 --> 00:29:27.020 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: They are a
taskmaster, but it's also deep.

00:29:27.020 --> 00:29:29.480 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's talk
about the depth or nature

00:29:29.480 --> 00:29:32.970 align:middle line:84%
of those messages, say, as
opposed to tarot, for example.

00:29:32.970 --> 00:29:33.770 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Sure.

00:29:33.770 --> 00:29:36.920 align:middle line:84%
Well, both of those
things have a tendency

00:29:36.920 --> 00:29:39.290 align:middle line:90%
to tap into the subconscious.

00:29:39.290 --> 00:29:44.810 align:middle line:84%
It just feels like with tarot
do a Celtic cross with 10 cards,

00:29:44.810 --> 00:29:48.050 align:middle line:84%
and you're going to mimic the
depth of any other language

00:29:48.050 --> 00:29:49.070 align:middle line:90%
of the divine.

00:29:49.070 --> 00:29:53.570 align:middle line:84%
But from a standpoint of here's
one card of tarot and one rune,

00:29:53.570 --> 00:29:55.520 align:middle line:84%
the depth of the
message from the rune

00:29:55.520 --> 00:29:59.480 align:middle line:84%
is going to be more significant
than the depth of the one card.

00:29:59.480 --> 00:30:00.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So just
by way of example,

00:30:00.980 --> 00:30:02.540 align:middle line:84%
tell us what that
might look like.

00:30:02.540 --> 00:30:05.360 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: Well, the rune
that I kept pulling was Perth.

00:30:05.360 --> 00:30:07.670 align:middle line:84%
And Perth is a
card that literally

00:30:07.670 --> 00:30:11.300 align:middle line:84%
talks about the need
for you to go deeper,

00:30:11.300 --> 00:30:17.820 align:middle line:84%
for you to go within and find
out exactly what is happening

00:30:17.820 --> 00:30:22.500 align:middle line:84%
within you and to understand
how that is fitting into what

00:30:22.500 --> 00:30:25.330 align:middle line:84%
you're doing at the moment now
that made a lot of sense to me.

00:30:25.330 --> 00:30:27.330 align:middle line:84%
I was writing "Compendium
of Magical Things."

00:30:27.330 --> 00:30:32.310 align:middle line:84%
And so, it was literally about,
Radleigh, come on step it up.

00:30:32.310 --> 00:30:33.980 align:middle line:90%
Step up your game.

00:30:33.980 --> 00:30:35.770 align:middle line:90%
Where are you going?

00:30:35.770 --> 00:30:38.080 align:middle line:84%
And what are you
going to do with this?

00:30:38.080 --> 00:30:40.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So with that, as
I was talking about earlier,

00:30:40.620 --> 00:30:42.330 align:middle line:84%
oftentimes, people
think, well, I

00:30:42.330 --> 00:30:45.160 align:middle line:84%
need to have some kind
of bead on this game

00:30:45.160 --> 00:30:47.330 align:middle line:84%
so I know how to interpret
what I'm seeing and all.

00:30:47.330 --> 00:30:49.710 align:middle line:90%
Do runes require interpretation?

00:30:49.710 --> 00:30:53.008 align:middle line:84%
Or are they very much
more direct messages?

00:30:53.008 --> 00:30:55.050 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: I think every
language of the divine

00:30:55.050 --> 00:30:56.820 align:middle line:90%
is interpretation.

00:30:56.820 --> 00:30:57.910 align:middle line:90%
I just do.

00:30:57.910 --> 00:31:02.100 align:middle line:84%
And I think that,
initially, I think

00:31:02.100 --> 00:31:04.680 align:middle line:84%
it's initially fine
to just go directly

00:31:04.680 --> 00:31:09.270 align:middle line:84%
to the specific message,
because you're learning.

00:31:09.270 --> 00:31:12.480 align:middle line:84%
And the thing,
Regina, is that we

00:31:12.480 --> 00:31:16.770 align:middle line:84%
have a tendency to want
to say, that's the magic.

00:31:16.770 --> 00:31:17.940 align:middle line:90%
The magic is the runes.

00:31:17.940 --> 00:31:18.960 align:middle line:90%
The magic is the cards.

00:31:18.960 --> 00:31:21.700 align:middle line:84%
The magic is the I
Ching or the pendulum.

00:31:21.700 --> 00:31:22.500 align:middle line:90%
We are the magic.

00:31:22.500 --> 00:31:23.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:31:23.430 --> 00:31:26.820 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: And I let my
students go there for a while,

00:31:26.820 --> 00:31:30.370 align:middle line:84%
because it gives
them confidence.

00:31:30.370 --> 00:31:33.120 align:middle line:84%
And if I push it back
on them too fast,

00:31:33.120 --> 00:31:35.920 align:middle line:84%
then they're going to go to
a lack of self-confidence.

00:31:35.920 --> 00:31:36.720 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:31:36.720 --> 00:31:37.460 align:middle line:90%
And that's important.

00:31:37.460 --> 00:31:38.200 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: And
not be empowered.

00:31:38.200 --> 00:31:39.790 align:middle line:90%
So I let them go there.

00:31:39.790 --> 00:31:43.500 align:middle line:84%
But as we go through this,
I bring it back to them.

00:31:43.500 --> 00:31:46.530 align:middle line:84%
Like this class
I just taught was

00:31:46.530 --> 00:31:48.540 align:middle line:84%
the last thing I
made them do was

00:31:48.540 --> 00:31:51.662 align:middle line:84%
they had to do a reading
with no cards, no pendulums.

00:31:51.662 --> 00:31:52.620 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Good for you.

00:31:52.620 --> 00:31:53.620 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: No nothing.

00:31:53.620 --> 00:31:54.510 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:31:54.510 --> 00:31:55.760 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: It was just them.

00:31:55.760 --> 00:31:57.315 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You are
the tuning device.

00:31:57.315 --> 00:31:59.315 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: And that was
the last thing we did.

00:31:59.315 --> 00:32:01.230 align:middle line:84%
And they blew it
out of the water.

00:32:01.230 --> 00:32:05.710 align:middle line:84%
So that they could see
it's the divine within you.

00:32:05.710 --> 00:32:07.260 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's wonderful.

00:32:07.260 --> 00:32:10.560 align:middle line:84%
I think that's a wonderful
way to cap that really.

00:32:10.560 --> 00:32:12.210 align:middle line:84%
Because in the
end, it is all us.

00:32:12.210 --> 00:32:13.670 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: It is.

00:32:13.670 --> 00:32:14.550 align:middle line:90%
We are the magic.

00:32:14.550 --> 00:32:15.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:32:15.420 --> 00:32:18.160 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes if we need a
little external reflection,

00:32:18.160 --> 00:32:19.410 align:middle line:90%
these are wonderful tools.

00:32:19.410 --> 00:32:20.368 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Excellent.

00:32:20.368 --> 00:32:23.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So this is one
that's little-known--

00:32:23.460 --> 00:32:25.710 align:middle line:84%
not so well-known in
the United States.

00:32:25.710 --> 00:32:26.640 align:middle line:90%
Then Lenormand.

00:32:26.640 --> 00:32:27.300 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: The Lenormand.

00:32:27.300 --> 00:32:27.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Lenormand.

00:32:27.960 --> 00:32:29.730 align:middle line:84%
And I was going to do an
interview a couple of years

00:32:29.730 --> 00:32:32.400 align:middle line:84%
ago on it in England and it
fell apart for some reason.

00:32:32.400 --> 00:32:34.710 align:middle line:84%
So please-- so I
didn't delve into it.

00:32:34.710 --> 00:32:36.870 align:middle line:10%
So what is Lenormand?

00:32:36.870 --> 00:32:38.790 align:middle line:10%
>>VALENTINE: It's 36 cards.

00:32:38.790 --> 00:32:40.920 align:middle line:10%
There are people who
adore the Lenormand,

00:32:40.920 --> 00:32:44.700 align:middle line:10%
and angels bless them.

00:32:44.700 --> 00:32:46.590 align:middle line:90%
It didn't resonate for me.

00:32:46.590 --> 00:32:48.960 align:middle line:84%
Not everything
resonates for everybody.

00:32:48.960 --> 00:32:50.670 align:middle line:84%
And the reason it
didn't resonate for me

00:32:50.670 --> 00:32:54.330 align:middle line:84%
is that people who
practice Lenormand say it's

00:32:54.330 --> 00:32:56.920 align:middle line:90%
easier than the other options.

00:32:56.920 --> 00:33:01.240 align:middle line:90%
I find it way more complex.

00:33:01.240 --> 00:33:04.290 align:middle line:84%
It actually came into
being because there

00:33:04.290 --> 00:33:07.170 align:middle line:84%
was a woman whose
name was Lenormand

00:33:07.170 --> 00:33:11.280 align:middle line:84%
who was a very famous
fortune teller, had

00:33:11.280 --> 00:33:14.180 align:middle line:90%
Marie Antoinette as a client.

00:33:14.180 --> 00:33:16.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: As most royalty do.

00:33:16.200 --> 00:33:19.920 align:middle line:84%
I mean, just as you had the
druids throughout the royalty

00:33:19.920 --> 00:33:21.550 align:middle line:90%
of Britain.

00:33:21.550 --> 00:33:23.880 align:middle line:84%
They always had their
druid by their side.

00:33:23.880 --> 00:33:27.210 align:middle line:84%
I mean, having
wise people, seers,

00:33:27.210 --> 00:33:29.580 align:middle line:84%
those who can read
cards, has always

00:33:29.580 --> 00:33:32.810 align:middle line:84%
been side-by-side, it seems,
with the royal traditions.

00:33:32.810 --> 00:33:33.810 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Absolutely.

00:33:33.810 --> 00:33:34.350 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:33:34.350 --> 00:33:35.150 align:middle line:90%
That's true.

00:33:35.150 --> 00:33:38.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: To foresee what your
next move is strategically.

00:33:38.160 --> 00:33:40.410 align:middle line:84%
You're in war, or whose land
you're going to take or--

00:33:40.410 --> 00:33:40.950 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: Who am
I going to marry?

00:33:40.950 --> 00:33:41.736 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --who's
going to take yours.

00:33:41.736 --> 00:33:42.570 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:33:42.570 --> 00:33:43.740 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Right.

00:33:43.740 --> 00:33:46.230 align:middle line:84%
Well, nevertheless,
she was very famous,

00:33:46.230 --> 00:33:47.430 align:middle line:90%
and she was very well-known.

00:33:47.430 --> 00:33:50.040 align:middle line:90%
And she passed over.

00:33:50.040 --> 00:33:53.490 align:middle line:84%
And so a lot of
different companies

00:33:53.490 --> 00:33:59.670 align:middle line:84%
that made cards said, oh,
here's Madame Lenormand's cards.

00:33:59.670 --> 00:34:01.290 align:middle line:90%
We've recreated them.

00:34:01.290 --> 00:34:03.570 align:middle line:90%
Well, that was a lie, OK?

00:34:03.570 --> 00:34:04.410 align:middle line:90%
They weren't.

00:34:04.410 --> 00:34:06.930 align:middle line:84%
She actually did something
called cartomancy, which

00:34:06.930 --> 00:34:09.389 align:middle line:90%
is reading with playing cards.

00:34:09.389 --> 00:34:10.570 align:middle line:90%
So they were not hers.

00:34:10.570 --> 00:34:11.370 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yeah.

00:34:11.370 --> 00:34:13.610 align:middle line:84%
And that went on to
become its own thing, too.

00:34:13.610 --> 00:34:14.020 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: And it is.

00:34:14.020 --> 00:34:14.340 align:middle line:90%
Still is.

00:34:14.340 --> 00:34:14.639 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:34:14.639 --> 00:34:14.980 align:middle line:90%
It is.

00:34:14.980 --> 00:34:15.540 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:34:15.540 --> 00:34:17.190 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: And
so these companies

00:34:17.190 --> 00:34:20.560 align:middle line:84%
started trying to
capitalize on her passing.

00:34:20.560 --> 00:34:23.489 align:middle line:84%
And so they came out
with the Lenormand.

00:34:23.489 --> 00:34:26.100 align:middle line:84%
And the Lenormand,
they're very simple cards.

00:34:26.100 --> 00:34:30.190 align:middle line:84%
They're cards like the
key, and the fox, the book.

00:34:30.190 --> 00:34:33.900 align:middle line:84%
Each one of these cards has
a lot of different meanings.

00:34:33.900 --> 00:34:38.280 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, some of those
meanings all seem to relate,

00:34:38.280 --> 00:34:43.749 align:middle line:84%
and then it'll just out
of nowhere throw in a M

00:34:43.749 --> 00:34:46.219 align:middle line:84%
And you're like, where
did that come from?

00:34:46.219 --> 00:34:49.080 align:middle line:84%
It's like the star,
it's dreams coming true

00:34:49.080 --> 00:34:51.190 align:middle line:84%
and all these things
all seem to make sense.

00:34:51.190 --> 00:34:53.460 align:middle line:84%
And then it also
means electricity.

00:34:53.460 --> 00:34:56.070 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, uh, what?

00:34:56.070 --> 00:34:58.140 align:middle line:84%
The most famous way
of reading Lenormands

00:34:58.140 --> 00:34:59.417 align:middle line:90%
is to use all 36 cards.

00:34:59.417 --> 00:35:00.875 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: So
I'm think, intense.

00:35:00.875 --> 00:35:01.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Wow, that's too much.

00:35:01.580 --> 00:35:01.950 align:middle line:90%
Too much information.

00:35:01.950 --> 00:35:03.080 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: That's intense.

00:35:03.080 --> 00:35:03.330 align:middle line:90%
Intense.

00:35:03.330 --> 00:35:04.290 align:middle line:90%
It's a lot.

00:35:04.290 --> 00:35:07.530 align:middle line:84%
And much like astrology,
which has houses--

00:35:07.530 --> 00:35:11.340 align:middle line:84%
so the where the planets land
means something different

00:35:11.340 --> 00:35:13.500 align:middle line:90%
based on which house it is in--

00:35:13.500 --> 00:35:19.740 align:middle line:84%
the Lenormand, the Grand
Tableau, where each card landed

00:35:19.740 --> 00:35:21.140 align:middle line:90%
changes its meaning.

00:35:21.140 --> 00:35:21.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:35:21.940 --> 00:35:22.200 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:35:22.200 --> 00:35:23.158 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: So, right?

00:35:23.158 --> 00:35:24.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I'm tired.

00:35:24.020 --> 00:35:24.750 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: I have a headache.

00:35:24.750 --> 00:35:24.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:35:24.840 --> 00:35:25.640 align:middle line:90%
I'm tired.

00:35:25.640 --> 00:35:26.820 align:middle line:90%
Let's move on, OK?

00:35:26.820 --> 00:35:30.138 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for sharing.

00:35:30.138 --> 00:35:31.680 align:middle line:84%
You touched on
something a moment ago

00:35:31.680 --> 00:35:36.060 align:middle line:84%
that I actually really enjoy,
which is the whole destiny

00:35:36.060 --> 00:35:37.230 align:middle line:90%
card, love card thing--

00:35:37.230 --> 00:35:40.830 align:middle line:84%
still based on the playing deck
and the interpretations there.

00:35:40.830 --> 00:35:43.050 align:middle line:84%
And I find those
kind of fun when

00:35:43.050 --> 00:35:45.540 align:middle line:84%
you look at the back and
their little compatibility

00:35:45.540 --> 00:35:47.340 align:middle line:90%
charts and such.

00:35:47.340 --> 00:35:48.510 align:middle line:90%
And so through the years--

00:35:48.510 --> 00:35:50.760 align:middle line:84%
I have a cousin who was
really into all of that.

00:35:50.760 --> 00:35:53.390 align:middle line:84%
And so she'd bring it around,
talking about this and that,

00:35:53.390 --> 00:35:55.590 align:middle line:84%
and I'd pay attention
here and there.

00:35:55.590 --> 00:35:57.870 align:middle line:84%
And I found that that
part of it actually

00:35:57.870 --> 00:36:01.380 align:middle line:84%
seemed to have some real truth
coming out of it in terms

00:36:01.380 --> 00:36:04.770 align:middle line:84%
of the compatibility, via
the numbers and the suits,

00:36:04.770 --> 00:36:07.040 align:middle line:90%
of you and another human being.

00:36:07.040 --> 00:36:07.840 align:middle line:90%
So I don't know.

00:36:07.840 --> 00:36:11.460 align:middle line:84%
What is your experience
with destiny cards?

00:36:11.460 --> 00:36:14.350 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: I haven't worked
with them all that much.

00:36:14.350 --> 00:36:18.100 align:middle line:84%
I do find that just like
any language of the divine,

00:36:18.100 --> 00:36:18.900 align:middle line:90%
it's the faith.

00:36:18.900 --> 00:36:24.600 align:middle line:84%
And so if that is what draws
you and you believe in it

00:36:24.600 --> 00:36:25.898 align:middle line:90%
and you trust it--

00:36:25.898 --> 00:36:27.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It really
does come down to that.

00:36:27.690 --> 00:36:28.870 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: It does
come down to that.

00:36:28.870 --> 00:36:31.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because you're
the information source.

00:36:31.200 --> 00:36:33.030 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: People
ask me why this works.

00:36:33.030 --> 00:36:34.613 align:middle line:84%
Well, there's the
spark of the divine,

00:36:34.613 --> 00:36:37.380 align:middle line:84%
but also, the I Ching is
thousands of years old--

00:36:37.380 --> 00:36:38.250 align:middle line:90%
thousands.

00:36:38.250 --> 00:36:41.370 align:middle line:84%
And so that means,
think of this as,

00:36:41.370 --> 00:36:43.980 align:middle line:84%
from a spiritual, metaphysical
standpoint, people

00:36:43.980 --> 00:36:46.500 align:middle line:90%
walking through a garden.

00:36:46.500 --> 00:36:49.200 align:middle line:84%
Over the years,
they have learned--

00:36:49.200 --> 00:36:51.660 align:middle line:84%
people have come
together and learned,

00:36:51.660 --> 00:36:54.330 align:middle line:84%
this is the best way to
go through this garden.

00:36:54.330 --> 00:36:55.530 align:middle line:90%
It's the most scenic.

00:36:55.530 --> 00:36:56.640 align:middle line:90%
It's the most lovely.

00:36:56.640 --> 00:36:58.320 align:middle line:90%
It's the most heartwarming.

00:36:58.320 --> 00:37:00.330 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it's the
shortest distance.

00:37:00.330 --> 00:37:02.220 align:middle line:90%
And we've worn a path.

00:37:02.220 --> 00:37:05.490 align:middle line:84%
So from a spiritual standpoint,
these languages of the divine

00:37:05.490 --> 00:37:10.730 align:middle line:84%
have worn a path
between us and source.

00:37:10.730 --> 00:37:13.070 align:middle line:84%
Because all of these
people-- millions

00:37:13.070 --> 00:37:15.850 align:middle line:84%
and millions and millions of
people have lent their faith.

00:37:15.850 --> 00:37:17.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, it creates
a field of resonance.

00:37:17.850 --> 00:37:18.300 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: It does.

00:37:18.300 --> 00:37:18.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:37:18.950 --> 00:37:19.750 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:37:19.750 --> 00:37:22.240 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, I mean, it's just
another one-- love cards,

00:37:22.240 --> 00:37:23.480 align:middle line:90%
destiny cards.

00:37:23.480 --> 00:37:27.150 align:middle line:84%
That's a quick and easy-- it's
the opposite of the Lenormand.

00:37:27.150 --> 00:37:27.950 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:37:27.950 --> 00:37:28.250 align:middle line:90%
You just look it up--

00:37:28.250 --> 00:37:28.750 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: The anti-Lenormand.

00:37:28.750 --> 00:37:29.917 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: --and you're done.

00:37:29.917 --> 00:37:31.235 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:37:31.235 --> 00:37:32.930 align:middle line:90%
If you're not a patient person.

00:37:32.930 --> 00:37:35.930 align:middle line:84%
One thing I want to
talk about is names.

00:37:35.930 --> 00:37:38.700 align:middle line:84%
Because we choose our
names before birth.

00:37:38.700 --> 00:37:39.500 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Yes.

00:37:39.500 --> 00:37:42.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I love that subject
because I have, in the past,

00:37:42.350 --> 00:37:45.470 align:middle line:84%
if it's someone very, very
close to me, or as a favor,

00:37:45.470 --> 00:37:48.060 align:middle line:84%
I'll do baby readings in the
week before a baby's born.

00:37:48.060 --> 00:37:50.270 align:middle line:84%
And get information from
them, and they'll talk to me

00:37:50.270 --> 00:37:51.830 align:middle line:90%
about names and other things.

00:37:51.830 --> 00:37:53.600 align:middle line:84%
But you're on the
same page here,

00:37:53.600 --> 00:37:55.160 align:middle line:90%
that we choose our parents.

00:37:55.160 --> 00:37:56.810 align:middle line:90%
We choose our name.

00:37:56.810 --> 00:37:59.850 align:middle line:84%
And I think this is important
information to know.

00:37:59.850 --> 00:38:02.810 align:middle line:84%
So first of all, yours
is not your Sedona name.

00:38:02.810 --> 00:38:04.242 align:middle line:90%
You are Radleigh Valentine.

00:38:04.242 --> 00:38:05.950 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: And it's
not my Sedona name.

00:38:05.950 --> 00:38:06.670 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love it.

00:38:06.670 --> 00:38:06.770 align:middle line:90%
I've only known--

00:38:06.770 --> 00:38:08.100 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: No, I really
am Radleigh Valentine.

00:38:08.100 --> 00:38:10.058 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --one other
person with the last name

00:38:10.058 --> 00:38:12.230 align:middle line:84%
of Valentine, which I
thought was a fortunate name.

00:38:12.230 --> 00:38:17.930 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about how a
being inspires their parents

00:38:17.930 --> 00:38:21.380 align:middle line:84%
to embrace and then put
on a birth certificate

00:38:21.380 --> 00:38:23.510 align:middle line:90%
a name that they want as a soul.

00:38:23.510 --> 00:38:24.470 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Right.

00:38:24.470 --> 00:38:28.388 align:middle line:84%
Well, so I believe that,
when we are on the other--

00:38:28.388 --> 00:38:30.680 align:middle line:84%
well, I have all kinds of
beliefs about the other side.

00:38:30.680 --> 00:38:32.055 align:middle line:84%
But when we're on
the other side,

00:38:32.055 --> 00:38:33.680 align:middle line:84%
one of the things
that we want to do

00:38:33.680 --> 00:38:37.400 align:middle line:84%
is to be in an
energetic alignment.

00:38:37.400 --> 00:38:39.360 align:middle line:90%
We want to set the stage.

00:38:39.360 --> 00:38:44.720 align:middle line:84%
We don't want to come to
Earth with an operating

00:38:44.720 --> 00:38:48.260 align:middle line:84%
system of Windows 7
when, really, Windows 10

00:38:48.260 --> 00:38:49.230 align:middle line:90%
is the way to go.

00:38:49.230 --> 00:38:50.030 align:middle line:90%
All right?

00:38:50.030 --> 00:38:53.520 align:middle line:84%
So this is almost like
our operating system.

00:38:53.520 --> 00:38:57.450 align:middle line:84%
So we're choosing our
time and place of birth

00:38:57.450 --> 00:39:00.140 align:middle line:90%
so that the astrology is right.

00:39:00.140 --> 00:39:03.950 align:middle line:84%
We're choosing our name so
that the numerology is right.

00:39:03.950 --> 00:39:07.760 align:middle line:84%
These things having
energetic effects upon us,

00:39:07.760 --> 00:39:12.250 align:middle line:84%
and the way we move through
the metaphorical video

00:39:12.250 --> 00:39:14.113 align:middle line:90%
game that is life.

00:39:14.113 --> 00:39:15.530 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So how
does this happen?

00:39:15.530 --> 00:39:17.720 align:middle line:84%
Tell people, on a
social level, how

00:39:17.720 --> 00:39:20.282 align:middle line:84%
do you get that name, as
a soul about to incarnate,

00:39:20.282 --> 00:39:21.990 align:middle line:84%
to your parents if
they haven't already--

00:39:21.990 --> 00:39:22.625 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Oh, to the parents.

00:39:22.625 --> 00:39:24.260 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --a close attachment
to a name that they're

00:39:24.260 --> 00:39:25.552 align:middle line:90%
going to choose no matter what.

00:39:25.552 --> 00:39:27.980 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: I think angels
are whispering in their ears.

00:39:27.980 --> 00:39:30.920 align:middle line:84%
I mean, my sister,
when she was getting

00:39:30.920 --> 00:39:33.650 align:middle line:84%
ready to give birth to
my nephew, had decided,

00:39:33.650 --> 00:39:35.720 align:middle line:90%
his name is Kolton.

00:39:35.720 --> 00:39:37.532 align:middle line:90%
I mean, we're done.

00:39:37.532 --> 00:39:38.990 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We are
not up for debate.

00:39:38.990 --> 00:39:40.532 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: We're
not up for debate.

00:39:40.532 --> 00:39:41.650 align:middle line:90%
His name is Kolton.

00:39:41.650 --> 00:39:45.260 align:middle line:90%
We're starting to monogram crap.

00:39:45.260 --> 00:39:48.820 align:middle line:84%
And she comes out of childbirth
and says, here's Thaniel.

00:39:48.820 --> 00:39:49.620 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:39:49.620 --> 00:39:50.420 align:middle line:90%
>>VALENTINE: Right?

00:39:50.420 --> 00:39:51.770 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And this does happen.

00:39:51.770 --> 00:39:52.943 align:middle line:90%
It happens a lot.

00:39:52.943 --> 00:39:54.360 align:middle line:84%
>>VALENTINE: It
does happen a lot.

00:39:54.360 --> 00:39:55.420 align:middle line:90%
And I think that's--

